description: David Murray and Jawole Willa Jo Zollar (Urban Bush Women) discuss Soul Deep, a collaborative project between the dance company and the David Murray Octet. Co-commissioned by the Walker, the multipart work includes structured and improvised movement and music as well as texts by Langston Hughes and Ntozake Shange. Walker senior performing arts curator Philip Bither hosts the conversation.
